  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling funds from their employer. However, taking into account the lack of a prior criminal record and the good faith effort demonstrated by partially repaying the stolen amount, a lengthy prison sentence is not strictly warranted. A short period of incarceration, followed by supervised probation and an order for full restitution, strikes the appropriate balance between punishment, deterrence, and allowing the defendant to remain a productive member of society to pay off the remaining debt.",
  "verdict": 6
}
